text: Ahmad Obeidat (born 18 November 1938) is a Jordanian politician. He was Prime Minister of Jordan from 10 January 1984 to 4 April 1985. He was born in Hartha, Irbid. In May 2011, he launched the National Front for Reform.Jordan Times ==References== Category:1938 births Category:Living people Category:Prime Ministers of Jordan
